"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-09-05-transfer-nigeria-youngster-joins-greek-club-olympiacos\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigerian youngster Taiye Abdulateef has joined Greek giants Olympiacos on a four-year contract.  The striker joined Olympiacos from Unicorns Football Academy.  The academy is owned by Super Eagles and Nottingham Forest forward, Taiwo Awoniyi.  Abdulateef will train with Olympiacos' U-19 side from where he is expected to graduate to the first team.  The young hitman is hopeful of making a big impact with the current UEFA Europa Conference League champions.  \\\"I hope to achieve as much success as possible and hopefully pave way for others at the Academy in Ilorin,\\\" he said during his unveiling ceremony.  Awoniyi stated:\\\"We prioritise the right environment for our players. Taiye can grow and progress here.\\\"      EPL: FIFPro reveals reason for Haaland's 'machine-like' start to new season  James signs two-year contract with Ikorodu City  Transfer: Club Brugge plot move for Fernandez  Transfer: Premier League clubs interested in Nigerian-born goalkeeper  Transfer: Rangers line up summer move for Sanusi  Transfer: Nwabali not concerned over free agent status  Transfer: Onazi moves to Lithuanian club FK Babrungas  Transfer: Barcelona eyes Chelsea's Pedro Neto as alternative to Marcus Rashford  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"